{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "EK100 (Damen et al., 2022) extends EK55 to 45 kitchens, with almost 100 h of video and 89,977 annotated action segments.",
    "The UDA setting of EK100 is defined as two domains, Source (containing labeled training data from 16 participants collected in 2018) and Target (i.e., unlabeled videos from the same 16 participants in the same kitchens but collected 2 years later).",
    "The segments are annotated with 97 nouns and 300 verbs corresponding to 3369 unique action classes, largely unbalanced and characterised by a long-tailed distribution.",
    "The UCF-HMDB dataset (Chen et al., 2019) was published to study video domain adaptation in third-person action classification.",
    "The dataset consists of 3209 videos from the original UCF101 (Soomro et al., 2012) and HMDB51 (Kuehne et al., 2011) datasets, which define the source and target domains used in DG e UDA."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "EK100 (Damen et al., 2022) extends EK55 to 45 kitchens, with almost 100 h of video and 89,977 annotated action segments.",
    "The UCF-HMDB dataset (Chen et al., 2019) was published to study video domain adaptation in third-person action classification.",
    "The dataset consists of 3209 videos from the original UCF101 (Soomro et al., 2012) and HMDB51 (Kuehne et al., 2011) datasets, which define the source and target domains used in DG e UDA."
